### Check Prime Numbers in an Array

Write a JavaScript function that takes an array of 5 numbers as input and checks if any of the numbers is a valid prime number. If it is, print the number to the console.

**Function Definition:**
```javascript
function checkPrimeNumbers(arr) {
  // Loop through the array
  for (let i = 0; i < arr.length; i++) {
    // Check if the current number is prime
    if (isPrime(arr[i])) {
      console.log(arr[i]);
    }
  }
}
```

**Helper Function:**
```javascript
function isPrime(num) {
  // Check if the number is less than 2
  if (num < 2) {
    return false;
  }

  // Check if the number is divisible by any number between 2 and its square root
  for (let i = 2; i <= Math.sqrt(num); i++) {
    if (num % i === 0) {
      return false;
    }
  }

  // If the number is not divisible by any number, it is prime
  return true;
}
```

**Example Usage:**
```javascript
// Example array
const arr = [2, 4, 6, 8, 10];

// Call the function
checkPrimeNumbers(arr);
```

**Output:**
```javascript
2
```

This function checks if any of the numbers in the input array is a prime number. If it is, it prints the number to the console.

